i-probe.e2e.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-compatible-chat-tools.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openwebui-probe.e2e.test.ts`\n- `git diff --cached --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: HTTP/API script proof is now represented as QA Lab scenario evidence with primary taxonomy IDs instead of only living under `test/scripts`.\n\nReal environment tested: Local source checkout on this branch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Focused Vitest commands listed above, QA coverage report command listed above, oxfmt check, staged whitespace check, and local autoreview.\n\nEvidence after fix: QA coverage report returned 126 scenarios, 172 coverage IDs, 106 primary coverage IDs, 0 missing coverage IDs, 0 unknown taxonomy IDs, and 28 fulfilled taxonomy features. The target IDs `tool-invocation-api`, `openai-compatible-apis`, `reasoning-and-cache-controls`, `openai-native-web-search`, and `web-search-and-fetch` are fulfilled.\n\nObserved result after fix: Focused tests passed across tooling, e2e, and extension-qa Vitest shards; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nWhat was not tested: The live Docker lanes `test:docker:openai-chat-tools`, `test:docker:openai-web-search-minimal`, and `test:docker:openwebui` were not run locally.\n\n\n",
